# BitNet-MLX: Aether Sovereign Edge SDK v16.0.0\
\
**Quantization-Aware Training (QAT), STE Gradient Routing & Hybrid Core Topologies**\
\
Engineered by JuniorCloud LLC. This matrix finalizes the SDK by introducing bidirectional kinematic updates. Autonomous 48V edge nodes can now actively train and fine-tune $b1.58$ manifolds using Straight-Through Estimator (STE) kernels.\
\
## Core Advancements\
* **STE Gradient Bypassing**: $W_\{q\} = W + \\text\{stop\\_gradient\}(W_\{q\} - W)$. Preserves continuous gradients during QAT backward passes while executing discrete $\\\{-1, 0, 1\\\}$ forward projections.\
* **SVD-Zero Backend**: Explicitly prohibits SVD ($A = U \\Sigma V^T$) to prevent $O(N^3)$ computational collapse during edge-native training. Optimization scales purely on $O(N)$ Gamma Signal Inference.\
* **Autonomous Edge Orchestration**: Telemetry, compilation, and QAT fine-tuning are fully enclosed, enabling true local-first intelligence decoupled from centralized cloud matrices.\
\
